On the basis of ancient literary sources, the general concept and the function of myths are analyzed. The course will treat Greek cosmogonical system, the functions of the Gods, their role in different rituals and cult, as well as the heroic myths and their representation in Greek literature. Verbal and iconographical representations of Greek myths, as well as the reception of ancient mythology are regarded as well.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim is to introduce the main themes of ancient myths in literary texts, to compare different versions of myth, to treat the variations and contradictions in these, to give a separate overview of cosmogonic myths, heroic myths, myths related to gods, to introduce verbal and iconographical representations of Greek myths, to demonstrate the reception of ancient mythology.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Studens will learn about Greek cosmological system, the main characteristics of polytheistic religion and the functions of different Gods in social life. The skill in analyzing various versions of myths is developed. Students will get acquainted with the sources in which Greek myths have preserved (texts, sculptures etc.).
